definition: face/side/surface/aspect/top/classifier for flat surfaces such as drums, mirrors, flags etc

sentences.english: This old foreigner looks so familiar to me.
sentences.chinese: 這個外國老人怎麼那麼面熟。

sentences.english: I remebered his face , but I could not recall where I met him.
sentences.chinese: 他很面熟，但我想不起在什麼地方見過他。

sentences.english: Two or three of them look familiar .
sentences.chinese: 在這些人中有兩三個看上去面熟。

sentences.english: Two or three of them look familiar.
sentences.chinese: 他們當中有兩三個看上去面熟。

sentences.english: He looks so familiar but I can't remember his name.
sentences.chinese: 他看上去非常面熟，但我想不起他的名字來了。

sentences.english: You look familiar, but I can't place you.
sentences.chinese: 你看起來挺面熟的，但是我認不出你。

sentences.english: She looks familiar to me, but I don't remember her name.
sentences.chinese: 她看起來面熟，但我記不起她的名字了。

sentences.english: His face looks familiar. Seems he was introduced before somewhere.
sentences.chinese: 小盆友有點面熟，好像以前發帖介紹過他。

sentences.english: The man with a beard looks familiar.
sentences.chinese: 留山羊鬍的那個人看起來很面熟。

sentences.english: Your face looks familiar to me .
No. something looks very familiar about this bank.
sentences.chinese: 不，這間銀行的某些東西看起來很面熟。

sentences.english: GG: You look familiar to me.
The smile on his face looked familiar.
sentences.chinese: 他臉上的笑容讓人覺得他看起來很面熟。

definition: to recognize/to remember sth (or sb) on seeing it/to know
to resemble one another/to be alike/similar
erhua variant of 納悶|纳闷[na4 men4]
pleasing to the eye/nice to look at
